Today, Susan Rice, the Domestic Policy Advisor, and Cedric Richmond, the White House Public Engagement Director and Senior Advisor, held a virtual discussion with various youth advocates for community violence prevention. The participants discussed the intersectionality of gun violence, effective community-based violence interventions, and the importance of survivor-led and victim-centered policymaking in this area. Rice and Richmond thanked the participants for their role in raising awareness about gun violence as a public health crisis and emphasized President Biden's commitment to making communities safer and promoting equity in policymaking. The meeting included a diverse group of participants, particularly focusing on Black and Brown young people.